## ORM (Odoo 13 — transitional between 12 and 14)

- Python 3.6+ only; Python 2 support was dropped in 13.0. No `from __future__` polyfills.
- `@api.multi` was **removed in 13.0** (raises AttributeError; present only ≤12). Recordsets are the default — **no decorator** needed. Never introduce `@api.multi`, and replace any leftover occurrence (it will crash at import/call).
- `@api.one` was **removed in 13.0** (raises AttributeError; present only ≤12) — never introduce it. `@api.returns` **still exists in 13.0** (kept in `api.py` `__all__`); it was not removed.
- `@api.model` for class-level methods that do not need a recordset.
- `@api.model_create_multi` is **available** in 13.0 — use it for `create()` overrides so batch creates work. A single-record `@api.model` `create()` will silently break batch create paths.
- `@api.depends`, `@api.constrains`, `@api.onchange` as usual. `@api.depends` evaluation is stricter than in 12 — declare every dependency.
- Call `ensure_one()` when a method assumes one record.
- Use parameterized SQL only. Batch `write()` and `unlink()` operations.
- Document every `sudo()` with a one-line reason in code.
- Prefer ORM over SQL. When SQL writes are unavoidable, invalidate or refresh affected caches.

## Performance

- Avoid `search()` or `browse(id)` inside loops.
- Prefer `read_group(..., lazy=False)` for grouped counts and sums.
- Push filtering into domains; do not filter in Python after a broad search.
- Use `search_count()` instead of `len(search())`.
- Batch recordset work with `mapped`, `filtered`, grouped domains, and set operations.
- Keep computed fields prefetch-friendly; declare a complete `@api.depends`.
- Store computed fields only when they are searched, grouped, sorted, or repeatedly displayed at scale.

## Views and models

- Inheritance edits use `<xpath>` with `position="after|before|inside|replace|attributes"`.
- `attrs="{...}"` and `states="..."` are **still valid in 13** — keep using them for conditional `invisible` / `readonly` / `required`. (They are only removed in 17.0; do not pre-migrate.)
- Keep XML IDs stable across releases.
- Mail features still use `mail.thread` / `mail.activity.mixin` (no v2 mixin yet in 13).
- `account.invoice` was **removed in 13.0** and unified into `account.move` — the model is gone. Invoice-type lives in the `type` field on `account.move` (renamed `move_type` only in 14.0). Target accounting fields on `account.move`.
- Use `_sql_constraints` or `@api.constrains` for validation.

## Frontend

- jQuery + QWeb templates only. **OWL does not exist in 13.0** (introduced in 14.0). Do not write `.owl.xml` components or `@odoo-module` JS modules.
- JS lives under `static/src/js/` as `odoo.define('module.name', function (require) { ... })` AMD modules.
- Reuse `web.AbstractAction`, `FormController`, `FieldWidget` base classes from the legacy web module.

## Security and style

- Keep `ir.model.access.csv` and `ir.rule` aligned with new models.
- Raise `UserError` for business rules, `ValidationError` for invalid data.
- Use `_logger`, never `print()`.
- Imports order: stdlib, third-party, `odoo`, local — in that order.
- Respect multi-company and record rules unless the task explicitly requires privileged behaviour. `_check_company_auto` **exists in 13** (in `models.py`) but is opt-in — it defaults to `False` and only auto-checks on models/fields that set `check_company=True`, so guard company crossings manually where it is not enabled.

## Verification

- Module install/update: `{{PYTHON_BIN}} odoo-bin -u <module> --stop-after-init -d {{DEFAULT_DB}}`.
- Module tests: `--test-enable --test-tags /<module> --stop-after-init`.
- For algorithm correctness against real data, prefer `realdata_test.eval_orm_expression` and `consistency_check_eval` over UI-driven repro.
